107 static void rxBufferFillAscending(MXM_MONITORING_INSTANCE_s *pState) {
108  TEST_ASSERT(pState != NULL_PTR);
109  for (uint16_t i = 0u; i <= MXM_RX_BUFFER_LENGTH; i++) {
110  pState->rxBuffer[i] = i;
111  }
112 }

123 /*========== Test Cases =====================================================*/
124 void testRegistryInitiated(void) {
125  /* check once: should be initiated from init */
126  for (uint8_t i = 0u; i < MXM_MAXIMUM_NR_OF_MODULES; i++) {
127  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL(false, mxm_state.registry[i].connected);
128  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL(0u, mxm_state.registry[i].deviceAddress);
129  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL(0u, mxm_state.registry[i].deviceID);
130  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL(MXM_MODEL_ID_NONE, mxm_state.registry[i].model);
131  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL(MXM_SILICON_VERSION_0, mxm_state.registry[i].siliconVersion);
132  }
133 
134  /* set some values to the registry */
135  mxm_state.registry[8].connected = true;
136  mxm_state.registry[15].deviceAddress = 42u;
137  mxm_state.registry[3].siliconVersion = 3u;
138  mxm_state.registry[30].model = 0x358;
139  mxm_state.registry[18].deviceID = 1414;
140 
141  /* call init again */
142  MXM_MonRegistryInit(&mxm_state);
143 
144  /* check a second time: should be initiated again */
145  for (uint8_t i = 0u; i < MXM_MAXIMUM_NR_OF_MODULES; i++) {
146  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL(false, mxm_state.registry[i].connected);
147  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL(0u, mxm_state.registry[i].deviceAddress);
148  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL(0u, mxm_state.registry[i].deviceID);
149  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL(MXM_MODEL_ID_NONE, mxm_state.registry[i].model);
150  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL(MXM_SILICON_VERSION_0, mxm_state.registry[i].siliconVersion);
151  }
152 }

162 void testRegistryConnectDevices(void) {
163  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL(STD_OK, MXM_MonRegistryConnectDevices(&mxm_state, 0));
164  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL(false, mxm_state.registry[0].connected);
165  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL(STD_OK, MXM_MonRegistryConnectDevices(&mxm_state, 1));
166  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL(true, mxm_state.registry[0].connected);
167  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL(STD_OK, MXM_MonRegistryConnectDevices(&mxm_state, MXM_MAXIMUM_NR_OF_MODULES));
168  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL(true, mxm_state.registry[MXM_MAXIMUM_NR_OF_MODULES - 1u].connected);
169 }

199 void testMXM_MonRegistryParseIdIntoDevicesCheckAscendingBufferId1(void) {
200  /* fill the buffer with ascending values and check at few places that the
201  parsing is consistent (always the same value) */
202  rxBufferFillAscending(&mxm_state);
203  const uint8_t highestDevice = 13u;
204  mxm_state.highest5xDevice = highestDevice;
205  MXM_MonRegistryConnectDevices(&mxm_state, highestDevice);
206  TEST_ASSERT_PASS_ASSERT(MXM_MonRegistryParseIdIntoDevices(
207  &mxm_state, (BATTERY_MANAGEMENT_TX_LENGTH_READALL + (2u * highestDevice)), MXM_REG_ID1));
208  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL(6938, mxm_state.registry[0].deviceID);
209  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL(6424, mxm_state.registry[1].deviceID);
210 }

247 void testMXM_MonRegistryParseVersionIntoDevicesCheckAscendingBuffer(void) {
248  /* fill the buffer with ascending values and check at few places that the
249  parsing is consistent (always the same value) */
250  rxBufferFillAscending(&mxm_state);
251  const uint8_t highestDevice = 13u;
252  mxm_state.highest5xDevice = highestDevice;
253  /* inject values so that satellite with highestDevice - 1u will report a model ID MXM_MODEL_ID_MAX17854 */
254  mxm_state.rxBuffer[3u] = 0x85u;
255  mxm_state.rxBuffer[2u] = 0x40u;
256  MXM_MonRegistryConnectDevices(&mxm_state, highestDevice);
257  TEST_ASSERT_PASS_ASSERT(MXM_MonRegistryParseVersionIntoDevices(
258  &mxm_state, (BATTERY_MANAGEMENT_TX_LENGTH_READALL + (2u * highestDevice))));
259  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL(MXM_MODEL_ID_invalid, mxm_state.registry[0].model); /*!< invalid model ID */
260  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL(8, mxm_state.registry[1].siliconVersion);
261  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL(MXM_MODEL_ID_MAX17854, mxm_state.registry[highestDevice - 1u].model);
262  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL(0, mxm_state.registry[highestDevice - 1u].siliconVersion);
263 }

278 void testMXM_MonRegistryParseStatusFmeaIntoDevicesCheckAscendingBuffer(void) {
279  /* fill the buffer with ascending values and check at few places that the
280  parsing is consistent (always the same value) */
281  rxBufferFillAscending(&mxm_state);
282  /* inject the "correct" register number (STATUS2) in the stream */
283  mxm_state.rxBuffer[1u] = MXM_REG_STATUS2;
284  const uint8_t highestDevice = 13u;
285  mxm_state.highest5xDevice = highestDevice;
286  MXM_MonRegistryConnectDevices(&mxm_state, highestDevice);
287  const uint8_t messageLength = (BATTERY_MANAGEMENT_TX_LENGTH_READALL + (2u * highestDevice));
288  TEST_ASSERT_PASS_ASSERT(MXM_MonRegistryParseStatusFmeaIntoDevices(&mxm_state, messageLength));
289  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL(0x1B1Au, mxm_state.registry[0u].registerStatus2);
290  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL(0x1918u, mxm_state.registry[1u].registerStatus2);
291  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL(0x0302u, mxm_state.registry[12u].registerStatus2);
292 
293  /* inject the "STATUS1" register number in the stream */
294  mxm_state.rxBuffer[1u] = MXM_REG_STATUS1;
295  TEST_ASSERT_PASS_ASSERT(MXM_MonRegistryParseStatusFmeaIntoDevices(&mxm_state, messageLength));
296  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL(0x1B1Au, mxm_state.registry[0u].registerStatus1);
297  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL(0x1918u, mxm_state.registry[1u].registerStatus1);
298  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL(0x0302u, mxm_state.registry[12u].registerStatus1);
299 
300  /* inject the "STATUS3" register number in the stream */
301  mxm_state.rxBuffer[1u] = MXM_REG_STATUS3;
302  TEST_ASSERT_PASS_ASSERT(MXM_MonRegistryParseStatusFmeaIntoDevices(&mxm_state, messageLength));
303  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL(0x1B1Au, mxm_state.registry[0u].registerStatus3);
304  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL(0x1918u, mxm_state.registry[1u].registerStatus3);
305  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL(0x0302u, mxm_state.registry[12u].registerStatus3);
306 
307  /* inject the "FMEA1" register number in the stream */
308  mxm_state.rxBuffer[1u] = MXM_REG_FMEA1;
309  TEST_ASSERT_PASS_ASSERT(MXM_MonRegistryParseStatusFmeaIntoDevices(&mxm_state, messageLength));
310  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL(0x1B1Au, mxm_state.registry[0u].registerFmea1);
311  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL(0x1918u, mxm_state.registry[1u].registerFmea1);
312  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL(0x0302u, mxm_state.registry[12u].registerFmea1);
313 
314  /* inject the "FMEA2" register number in the stream */
315  mxm_state.rxBuffer[1u] = MXM_REG_FMEA2;
316  TEST_ASSERT_PASS_ASSERT(MXM_MonRegistryParseStatusFmeaIntoDevices(&mxm_state, messageLength));
317  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL(0x1B1Au, mxm_state.registry[0u].registerFmea2);
318  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL(0x1918u, mxm_state.registry[1u].registerFmea2);
319  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL(0x0302u, mxm_state.registry[12u].registerFmea2);
320 }

330 /** check that #MXM_CheckIfADeviceHasBeenReset() recognizes a set ALRTRST bit */
331 void testMXM_CheckIfADeviceHasBeenReset(void) {
332  TEST_ASSERT_FAIL_ASSERT(MXM_CheckIfADeviceHasBeenReset(NULL_PTR));
333 
334  const uint8_t highestDevice = 10u;
335  MXM_MonRegistryConnectDevices(&mxm_state, highestDevice);
336  /* place fake cleared register values */
337  for (uint8_t i = 0u; i < highestDevice; i++) {
338  mxm_state.registry[i].registerStatus1 = 0u;
339  }
340  /* therefore, no device should be reset */
341  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL(false, MXM_CheckIfADeviceHasBeenReset(&mxm_state));
342 
343  /* fake one device being reset */
344  mxm_state.registry[0u].registerStatus1 = 0x4000u;
345  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL(true, MXM_CheckIfADeviceHasBeenReset(&mxm_state));
346 }

354 /** check if #MXM_CheckIfADeviceIsConnected() does its job */
355 void testMXM_CheckIfADeviceIsConnected(void) {
356  for (uint8_t checkedDevice = 0u; checkedDevice < MXM_MAXIMUM_NR_OF_MODULES; checkedDevice++) {
357  mxm_state.registry[checkedDevice].connected = false;
358  TEST_ASSERT_FALSE(MXM_CheckIfADeviceIsConnected(&mxm_state, checkedDevice));
359  mxm_state.registry[checkedDevice].connected = true;
360  TEST_ASSERT_TRUE(MXM_CheckIfADeviceIsConnected(&mxm_state, checkedDevice));
361  }
